      "description": "Four-loop equal-mass banana (sunrise) integral in $D=2-2\\varepsilon$. Associated to a Calabi-Yau 3-fold (CY operator #34 in Almkvist et al.). First Feynman integral related to a non-trivial CY manifold for which an epsilon-factorised differential equation is established. Five master integrals; the construction uses a 'Yukawa coupling' function $K$ arising from the non-symmetric-product structure of the Picard-Fuchs operator. Nine-letter symbol alphabet defined in terms of q-expansion functions. Singular points at $y=-1,-1/9,-1/25$ (i.e. $p^2/m^2=1,9,25$).",
